The paper proposes a new method for sparse PCA, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. The approach is based on a recursive divide-and-conquer methodology, which is a common technique in computer science and optimization. The paper also discusses the convergence and computational complexity of the proposed algorithm, which are topics typically studied in the fields of numerical analysis and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
